{{EngvarB|date=July 2015}} {{Use dmy dates|date=July 2015}} {{Malay name|Eekmal|Ahmad}} {{Infobox officeholder | honorific-prefix = | name = Eekmal Ahmad | image = Eekmal_Ahmad.jpg | imagesize = | caption = | constituency_AM2 = | assembly2 = | majority2 = | term_start2 = | term_end2 = | predecessor2 = | successor2 = | constituency2 = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1980|2|28}} | birth_place = [[Alor Star]], [[Malaysia]] | residence = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]] | death_date = | death_place = | party = | occupation = Historian | relations = | spouse = | children = | website = |alma_mater = [[Sultan Abdul Hamid College]] [[Universiti Teknologi MARA]] }}
'''Eekmal Ahmad''' is a Malaysian politician and historian. He is also the former press secretary to former Opposition Leader of Malaysia, [[Anwar Ibrahim]]. Eekmal was [[Parti Keadilan Rakyat]] (PKR)'s candidate in the [[Malaysian general election, 2013|13th Malaysian general election]]. He contested against the former [[List of Menteris Besar of Kedah|Menteri Besar of Kedah]] [[Ahmad Bashah Md Hanipah]] but lost with a margin of 895 votes.<ref>http://www.astroawani.com/berita-politik/siapa-ahmad-bashah-menteri-besar-kedah-baharu-yang-menggantikan-mukhriz-mahathir-92675</ref>
== Personal background == He grew up in Alor Star, Kedah. He received his secondary education at [[Sultan Abdul Hamid College]] and had his university education at [[Universiti Teknologi MARA]], graduated with a bachelor's degree in law. He studied East Asian History in [[School of Oriental and African Studies]] at the [[University of London]] funded by the prestigious [[Chevening Scholarship]]. His MA dissertation focused on the formation of Chinese Nationalism during Xinhai period till May 4th Movement and its influences on Malaya.
After leaving university, Eekmal worked as Assistant Coordinator for Asian Renaissance: Capacity Building for Future Leaders in Southeast Asia based in Institute for Policy Research. He then worked as a translator at Middle Eastern Graduates Centre, an intellectual think-tank based in Kuala Lumpur. He then served as press secretary to Anwar Ibrahim from 2008 until 2012. He translated several works from English to Bahasa Melayu, among them, Thomas Paine's Rights of Man, Claude Addas' Voyage of No Return and FA Hayek's essay, Individualism True and False.
== Political career == In 2008, Eekmal joined Parti Keadilan Rakyat and was appointed as press secretary to [[Anwar Ibrahim]]. During the [[Malaysian general election, 2013|13th Malaysian general election]] in 2013, Eekmal was nominated as the PKR candidate for the state assembly seat of [[Bakar Bata (state constituency)|Bakar Bata]] in Kedah.<ref>http://www.themalaysianinsider.com/bahasa/article/pertembungan-antara-dua-generasi-di-dun-bakar-bata</ref> However he lost by a narrow margin to [[United Malays National Organisation]] (UMNO) veteran politician, Ahmad Bashah Md Hanipah who was the former Menteri Besar of Kedah.
